usbhid-dump
------------------------------------------
Usbhid-dump is a USB HID dumping utility based on libusb 1.0. It dumps USB HID
device report descriptors and reports themselves as they are being sent, for
all or specific device interfaces.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libusb1.0-1.0.21-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  libusb1.0-devel-1.0.21-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/DIGImend/usbhid-dump

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/DIGImend/usbhid-dump/archive/refs/tags/1.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack usbhid-dump-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./usbhid-dump-1.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/usbhid-dump-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/usbhid-dump-1.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(usbhid-dump)
  /usr/bin/usbhid-dump.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/usbhid-dump.README
  /usr/share/doc/usbhid-dump/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/usbhid-dump/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man8/usbhid-dump.8.gz

